Rating: 4
This was delicious. As an inexperienced cook, I wasn't able to get the lamb of the bone, so I just cooked it with. Eventually the meat came off the bone, so I didn't have to serve it with bones. Probably added some flavor. Only because I already had dried plums and dried apricots in the house, I used those to substitute the fig. The lemon, saffron, and ginger cut through the richness of the rest of it, so it's my favorite of the three different lamb stews I've made. I used the amount of chicken broth recommended, but it made it soupy. In the end I had to add some flour to thicken it. I served it with orzo. Big hit.

