Without a doubt the best lamb stew (or stew of any type) that I've ever made/had/dreamed of. I'll make this anytime I'm trying to impress someone-- and it's really very easy. I used lamb shoulder chops (that I deboned), because I had them in the freezer. I used a regular lemon also, worked fine. I also added a dash of red wine toward the end, which was nice, but I don't think necessary. Make sure you keep it simmering for at least the hour and a half-- it really will thicken the sauce, mellow the lemon, and mature the flavors. I wasn't convinced until I tasted the mature, simmered, sauce. You will need an iron will to keep from eating this all before your guests arrive. Served with fresh bread and couscous.

